Political Capital: Hungarian Guard Increases State Risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, founded this August with the support of the "Movement for a Better Hungary", have increased the risk of Hungary and the region in several ways.
Among other things, the Institute’s “Risk Assessment Report” states that in connection with the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk is the “intensification of the already existing ethnic tensions between the Gypsies and non-gypsy population in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic clashes in the short term”.
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which is probably aimed at provoking such an argument, according to the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure by the political leaders: "Persons of public life have left the discussion of the Roma question to representatives of radical political groups, who have now built their political strategy on the Roma-Hungarian opposition".
