Congress approves the MIFID directive, which came into force on November 1.
Parallel to the parliamentary drafting that ended its session today with the Congressional resolution in the Senate on the supplementary/amendment requests associated with the project, the government published the provisions that emerge from the new law, with the intention of allowing the entry into force of both regulations by the end of the year.
The representatives of the various companies unanimously praised the efforts of the congressmen and senators, who in their negotiations and votes had pursued the goal of establishing the best possible regime that ensures the safety of investors and regulates the individual entrepreneurial activities, in order to guarantee a generally efficient market.
In addition to modernising financial markets, MIFID, which re-establishes the securities services regime, is pursuing improvements in investor protection, increasing the Spanish Securities Commission’s (CNMV) control claim, and promoting cooperation between the various supervisory authorities of the European Union.
The new Directive allows financial advice to be offered to both specialised firms and natural or legal persons, and also contributes to the establishment of new financial services companies (ESIS), the consulting companies that join the investment and brokerage companies of securities.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of financial transactions, adding to regulated circulation markets the multilateral systems of securities trading and the systems for the internationalisation of trading orders, which would eventually compete with the current economic actors.
The law obliges investment companies to register the priorities of their company profile, the confrontation and the forms of dealing with risks in the market and all the projects carried out in order to facilitate the CNMV’s control task.
The Congressional Economic Commission subsequently made further changes, with the decision that the titled bond must now be considered a complex financial asset for the investor due to its high degree of risk, having been confirmed by the US mortgage and banking crisis.
In addition, the entry into force of the Directive on the legal restriction of the work of qualified economic scientists was used; 30 years after 1977, the Regulation was adopted, which restricted the work reserved for economic scientists.
The Senate, for its part, established new positions in the financial sector, such as that of the economic mediator, who works on a foreign account, does not require authorization from the CNMV and can simultaneously offer its services for the commercialization of products and for the extraction of customers to several investment companies.
