Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible damage caused by the driver, includes a high cost, the amount of which in turn depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driver's license, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are dealing with here.
A car insurance policy is an agreement between an insurance company and an insurer.
This agreement is entered into in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to present the corresponding severance amount in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance consisting of several factors, including age, gender, date of creation of the driver's license, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that in the event of a higher risk of accident, higher contribution payments become due.
For this reason, both over 25-year-olds and women have to make fewer contribution payments, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married people, since according to the statistical values and therefore also according to the conviction of the companies, they tend to have fewer accidents than single people.
The benefit attributed to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, the insurance companies must take into account a whole series of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to choose exactly the car insurance that is most likely to meet his personal needs.
At this point, we now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance, in order to be able to make not only a performance-, but also a price-oriented choice.
When choosing a low-cost insurance policy, those under the age of 25 face numerous obstacles, such as low driving practice and a young driver’s license.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out full insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
Cautious drivers can choose a full-face helmet with a deductible, so that the benefits of a full-face helmet insurance are covered, but offered at a low price.
This type of contract includes that the customer has to pay a part of the amount resulting from the damage himself.
The amount will be determined before the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid , explains Luis Noguera, chief representative of Spain at First Europe, a brokerage company for online insurance.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to the car itself.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you’re under 25, it’s up to you to lower your insurance costs, so your credit score increases by trying to drive cautiously and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the base rate at the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the said tariff.
The amount of credits and penalty payments depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it can afford to increase the bonus payments, Noguera explains.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract, which is due to the fact that with increasing driving practice, the accident rate decreases.
Thus, it makes the most sense to opt for a full-cash insurance with self-insurance.
Usually, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish head of the European company, adding that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice, after the fear of the novice has been removed.
Nevertheless, for a married customer who does not have children, it is advisable to take out full-cash insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the person concerned also allows.
On the part of the insurers, married couples with children are considered the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly, their contribution payments are also low.
In this case, a full insurance with a deductible (with an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, it is recommended to take out an extended insurance, which will only be used for the third year of the vehicle.
They are generally more relaxed and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to make a higher contribution, says Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is a good idea to take out full insurance with a deductible (with an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance, which only works with a sufficiently high credit score.
Ultimately, it must be noted that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver from possible accident damage, but also because it carries high costs, which require that a thorough selection be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
